schneier@chinet.chi.il.us (Bruce Schneier) writes:

>(1)  Alice and Bob mutually choose a prime p, in such a way that the
>factorization of p-1 is known.  (In reality, Alice and Bob will each
>generate a random prime, and then check if the product of the two primes
>plus 1 is prime.)

I must be slow too... unless one of Alice or Bob chooses 2 as their
prime, the product will always be odd, so the product plus 1 will be
even, and will never be prime.

